lead_paragraph: As both presidential candidates campaign against it, the White House is negotiating with Republicans in Congress to ratify the largest regional trade agreement ever.

headline.print_headline: Amid Opposition, T.P.P. Gets a Final Push
headline.main: Obama Readies One Last Push for Trans-Pacific Partnership

snippet: As both presidential candidates campaign against it, the White House is negotiating with Republicans in Congress to ratify the largest regional trade agreement ever....
abstract: Pres Obama, amid opposition, is planning final push for approval of Trans-Pacific Partnership, trade agreement with United States and 11 Pacific Rim nations; both Obama and congressional Republicans want to approve pact, but are delaying vote until after presidential election for fear of inciting even more rebuke from presidential nominees.
